{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VxTYaQe8GArqWfNF7ctUAX","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# SOAR-ARC -- Mission\n2\t\n3\t## Goal\n4\t\n5\tImprove the SOAR agent to solve as many ARC tasks as possible.\n6\t\n7\tThe agent uses a purely symbolic SOAR cognitive architecture. It discovers\n8\ttransformation rules from example pairs and applies them to test inputs.\n9\tLearned rules accumulate in `procedural_memory/` across tasks.\n10\t\n11\tThe infinite loop (`run_loop.sh`) feeds tasks to the agent, then invokes\n12\tClaude Code to analyze failures and add new generalization strategies.\n13\t\n14\t## Architecture\n15\t\n16\tSee **CLAUDE.md** for the full architecture, file structure, operator\n17\tpipeline, and design constraints. CLAUDE.md is the authoritative reference.\n18\t\n19\t## Design Principles (non-negotiable)\n20\t\n21\t- **Purely symbolic** -- no neural networks, no embeddings, no ML\n22\t- **SOAR is the only solver** -- no fallback engines or heuristics\n23\t- **Knowledge as relations** -- store why (relations), not how (programs)\n24\t- **Failure is information** -- impasses reveal what knowledge is missing\n25\t- **Memory-based learning** -- the agent reuses rules it discovered earlier\n26\t\n27\t## What Claude Code Should Do Each Session\n28\t\n29\t1. Read the learning loop output (which tasks passed/failed, what rules exist)\n30\t2. Pick failing tasks and read their JSON data\n31\t3. Understand the transformation pattern each task requires\n32\t4. Add generalization strategies to `agent/active_operators.py`:\n33\t   - `GeneralizeOperator._try_*()` -- detect the pattern from extracted diffs\n34\t   - `PredictOperator._apply_*()` -- apply the rule to produce output\n35\t5. Each strategy must handle a **category** of tasks, not a single task\n36\t6. Verify: `python run_task.py` must still output CORRECT\n37\t7. Append session results to `logs/session_log.md`\n38\t\n39\t## Do NOT Modify\n40\t\n41\t- `data/` -- ARC dataset (read-only)\n42\t- `agent/cycle.py` -- SOAR decision cycle\n43\t- `agent/wm.py` -- WorkingMemory\n44\t\n45\t## Entry Point\n46\t\n47\t```bash\n48\t./run_loop.sh\n49\t```\n50\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08abbe83-7a48-484c-9c1c-503e8fec076e","uuid":"cee99cb5-1abc-4e0e-b3eb-501b449748f9","timestamp":"2026-04-29T04:17:59.858Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sir_k/Desktop/SOAR-ARC-test/PROMPT.md","content":"# SOAR-ARC -- Mission\n\n## Goal\n\nImprove the SOAR agent to solve as many ARC tasks as possible.\n\nThe agent uses a purely symbolic SOAR cognitive architecture. It discovers\ntransformation rules from example pairs and applies them to test inputs.\nLearned rules accumulate in `procedural_memory/` across tasks.\n\nThe infinite loop (`run_loop.sh`) feeds tasks to the agent, then invokes\nClaude Code to analyze failures and add new generalization strategies.\n\n## Architecture\n\nSee **CLAUDE.md** for the full architecture, file structure, operator\npipeline, and design constraints. CLAUDE.md is the authoritative reference.\n\n## Design Principles (non-negotiable)\n\n- **Purely symbolic** -- no neural networks, no embeddings, no ML\n- **SOAR is the only solver** -- no fallback engines or heuristics\n- **Knowledge as relations** -- store why (relations), not how (programs)\n- **Failure is information** -- impasses reveal what knowledge is missing\n- **Memory-based learning** -- the agent reuses rules it discovered earlier\n\n## What Claude Code Should Do Each Session\n\n1. Read the learning loop output (which tasks passed/failed, what rules exist)\n2. Pick failing tasks and read their JSON data\n3. Understand the transformation pattern each task requires\n4. Add generalization strategies to `agent/active_operators.py`:\n   - `GeneralizeOperator._try_*()` -- detect the pattern from extracted diffs\n   - `PredictOperator._apply_*()` -- apply the rule to produce output\n5. Each strategy must handle a **category** of tasks, not a single task\n6. Verify: `python run_task.py` must still output CORRECT\n7. Append session results to `logs/session_log.md`\n\n## Do NOT Modify\n\n- `data/` -- ARC dataset (read-only)\n- `agent/cycle.py` -- SOAR decision cycle\n- `agent/wm.py` -- WorkingMemory\n\n## Entry Point\n\n```bash\n./run_loop.sh\n```\n","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":50}}}
