e hits: 38\n1521\t- Time: 20s\n1522\t- Log: logs/learn_20260429_130550.log\n1523\t\n1524\t---\n1525\t## Learning Loop -- 2026-04-29 13:16\n1526\t\n1527\t- Split: None, Tasks: 40\n1528\t- Correct: 40 / 40 (100.0%)\n1529\t- Rules: 77 -> 78 (+1 learned)\n1530\t- Stored rule hits: 38\n1531\t- Time: 20s\n1532\t- Log: logs/learn_20260429_131637.log\n1533\t\n1534\t---\n1535\t## Session 32 -- 2026-04-29 (afe3afe9)\n1536\t\n1537\tPicked the only INCORRECT task: `afe3afe9`.\n1538\t\n1539\tDecoded transformation:\n1540\t- 30x30 input has a single full row/col of color 1 ('gravity indicator')\n1541\t  on one of the four borders.\n1542\t- The remaining region holds a regularly spaced 7x7 cell-grid where each\n1543\t  cell is either bg or a 3x3 hollow square of one color (border = color,\n1544\t  centre = 0), separated by 1-pixel bg gaps.\n1545\t- Output is the cell-grid, with fully-empty cell rows/cols pruned and\n1546\t  gravity applied based on the 1-line position:\n1547\t    1-line TOP    -> gravity RIGHT  (per row)\n1548\t    1-line BOTTOM -> gravity LEFT   (per row)\n1549\t    1-line LEFT   -> gravity UP     (per col)\n1550\t    1-line RIGHT  -> gravity DOWN   (per col)\n1551\t\n1552\tStrategy added: `_try_hollow_square_gravity` /\n1553\t`_apply_hollow_square_gravity` (uses shared static\n1554\t`_compute_hollow_square_gravity_output` helper). Parameter-free: succeeds\n1555\tonly when the deterministic decode reproduces every training output.\n1556\tRestrictive guards: full-border 1-line, exact 3x3 hollow-square shape per\n1557\tnon-empty cell, 3x3 all-bg per empty cell, >=2x2 cell-grid after pruning.\n1558\t\n1559\tVerification:\n1560\t- `python run_task.py` (regression on 08ed6ac7): CORRECT\n1561\t- `python run_learn.py --limit 40 --shuffle`: 40 / 40 (100.0%) (was 39/40)\n1562\t- afe3afe9 now solves via pipeline -> hollow_square_gravity rule\n1563\t- Rules: 77 -> 78 (rule_078 = hollow_square_gravity for afe3afe9)\n1564\t\n1565\t---\n1566\t## Learning Loop -- 2026-04-29 13: